.\" Manpage for cmd-memo
.TH CMD-MEMO 1 "2025" "Linux Zen Assistance" "Command Memo Manager"

.SH NAME
cmd-memo \- Command memo manager for Linux

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cmd-memo
.I <command> [arguments]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cmd-memo
is a lightweight and efficient Bash tool that allows you to store, organize and search your Linux commands.
It uses a clean TSV (Tab-Separated Values) file to maintain a technical memory that is easy to browse and update.

The tool supports:
.IP \[bu] 2
Adding, editing and deleting entries
.IP \[bu] 2
Searching across categories, command names, levels and descriptions
.IP \[bu] 2
Dynamic category management (add, rename, delete)
.IP \[bu] 2
A readable and versionable data format without external dependencies

cmd-memo is part of the Linux Zen Assistance toolkit.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B categ | -c
List all categories present in the category file.

.TP
.B list | -l <category>
List all commands inside a category.

.TP
.B search | -s <text>
Search for a string in category, level, command or detail fields.

.TP
.B add | -a
Add a new memo entry (interactive mode).

.TP
.B edit | -e <command>
Edit an entry by exact command name.

.TP
.B delete | -d <command>
Delete an entry by exact command name.

.TP
.B addcateg | -A
Add a new category.

.TP
.B renamecateg | -R <old> <new>
Rename a category.

.TP
.B deletecateg | -D <category>
Delete a category.  
If it contains commands, they must be reassigned to another category.

.TP
.B help | -h | --help
Display help message.

.SH DATA FILES

.TP
.B cmd-memo.tsv
Main TSV database containing all memo entries.

.TP
.B cmd-memo.categ
List of valid categories used by the program.

Both files are stored in the same directory as the script when using manual installation.

.SH TSV FORMAT

Each entry consists of four fields separated by TAB characters:

.IP
category<TAB>level<TAB>command<TAB>detail

.IP
\fBcategory\fR: logical group (system, network, backup...)  
\fBlevel\fR: "root" or "user"  
\fBcommand\fR: the actual command (unique identifier)  
\fBdetail\fR: description or comment

Example entry:

.IP
system<TAB>user<TAB>ls<TAB>List directory contents

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
List categories:
.IP
.B cmd-memo -c

.TP
List commands in "system":
.IP
.B cmd-memo -l system

.TP
Search for commands related to SSH:
.IP
.B cmd-memo -s ssh

.TP
Add a new entry:
.IP
.B cmd-memo -a

.TP
Rename a category:
.IP
.B cmd-memo -R oldname newname

